
[1]bowling-green

   BOWLING-GREEN, n. [bowl and green.] A level piece of ground kept smooth
   for bowling.

   1. In gardening, a parterre in a grove,laid with fine turf, with
   compartments of divers figures, with dwarf trees and other decorations.
   It may be used for bowling; but the French and Italians have such
   greens for ornament.
